ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A fast-paced and reading-focused tour through some key issues in micro- and macroeconomic development. I'd recommend auditing the first half of the class, and dropping out for the second.
I really loved most of this class but I'm not sure I could recommend it to another student because the second half was not very useful.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Prof. Udry's portion of the class provided some interesting and very useful insights into cutting edge research methods in microeconomic development.
This course renewed my faith that there is interesting and useful research on development out there!
